-- Rosneft Taps Former Exxon’s Runje for Exploration Head
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2012-12-12T07:43:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-12/rosneft-taps-former-exxon-s-runje-for-exploration-head.html
OAO Rosneft,  Russia ’s largest oil
producer, appointed Zeljko Runje, formerly of  Exxon Mobil Corp. (XOM) ,
as vice president for exploration and production, its press
service said.  Runje will continue to be responsible for offshore
projects, a position he was given in October, Rosneft said. Gani
Gilyaev, his predecessor, will head Rosneft’s Samaraneftegaz
unit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow at 
